Vegan Cauliflower Gratin
  --minimalist baker

1 medium cauliflower head, cut into florets (~7-8 c)
1 1/2 tbsp olive oil
1 c finely chopped onion (~1/2 onion)
4 cloves garlic, minced
2 tbsp cornstarch or arrowroot starch
14 oz can light coconut milk
1/8 tsp nutmeg
1 tbsp nooch (optional)
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp black pepper
1/3 c vegan parm

Preheat oven to 375F/190C. Cut cauliflower into small florets and steam for ~15 min until tender (test with fork). Set aside uncovered to cool slightly. Heat latge ovensafe skillet (cast iron, etc) over medium heat. Add oil and onion and saute until onion becomes tender and translucent, ~ 3-5 min. Add garlic and cook for 1 min or until fragrant, being careful not to let it burn. reduce heat to low. Add cornstarch and whisk to incorporate. Cook for 1 min. Pour in coconut milk a little at a time, whisking constantly to incorporate. Go slowly to prevent clumping. Conitue until all the milk has been added. Simmer for 8-10 min or until thickened, whisking frequently. Add nutmeg, nooch, salt, and pepper. Taste and adjust seasoning as needed; add nutmeg for warnth, nooch for cheesiness, or salt or pepper to taste. Mixture should be very cheesy and savory to season the cauliflower well. Add the steamed cauliflower to the sauce and toss thoroughly to coat. Taste once more and adjust as needed. If you didn't use oven safe skillet, can transfer to a 8x8" baking dish. Sprinkle top with parm and bake uncovered for 12-15 min until top is golden brown and crisp. Can broil for 1-2 min to get extra crisp.


